      <item>
        <title>Is the Mystic Meta Good or Bad?</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Navi]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>It should be entirely up to the players, but they should not feel obliged to do it.</p>
<p>It’s the quickest and most reliable way to solve the game for BD, but regardless of whether you find it an enjoyable way to play ToL, it shouldn’t ever become a requirement as a mystic or be considered gamethrowing if you choose not to participate in it as a BD. The only thing that can come from a decision like that is a smaller playerbase.</p>
<p>I definitely think mystic meta is bad. It places all decision making and deduction on a single player, while everyone else just does exactly what they’re told or gets executed for being unconfirmed.</p>
<p>It’d probably be better to just remove private matter from the game, but this sort of meta will always exist in some form as long as information can be communicated secretly. I’m not sure there’s any clean way to get rid of it without removing whispers completely, despite them having far more interesting uses other than sending all logs to a single player.</p>
          <p><a href="https://forum.throneoflies.com/t/is-the-mystic-meta-good-or-bad/77108/5">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
